headline: How Recent Developments Are Rewriting The General Mills Investment Story
summary: General Mills stock has seen its fair value estimate trimmed slightly from about $53.89 to $53.00, driven largely by a more conservative long term revenue growth outlook. With the discount rate ticking up from roughly 6.78% to 6.96% and long run revenue growth assumptions nudged a bit lower into slightly more negative territory, analysts are signaling a cautious but not dire reassessment of the company trajectory.
